<paragraph id="E97036DD3F18FF8FFF76FDC7FD52FDBD" blockId="45.[151,1437,577,1432]" box="[151,690,577,604]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Size. Reaches 
<quantity id="2E379B383F18FF8FFEDBFDC7FE66FDBD" box="[314,390,577,604]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
total length (Miller 1986).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F18FF8FFF26FDE3FEF2FA79" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F18FF8FFF26FDE3FF00FD0D" blockId="45.[151,1437,577,1432]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Morphology. D VI + I,9; A I,7–9; P 15–16. A very small species with a somewhat elongated body; head not particularly flattened. Caudal peduncle deep, almost as high as body. Caudal fin rounded. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFB69FD0FFA7CFD42" bold="true" box="[1160,1436,649,675]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">First dorsal fin pointed</emphasis>
(first spine longest), at least in males (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFDB0FD2BFD3DFD26" author="Miller, P. J." box="[593,733,685,711]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="395 - 407" refId="ref61269" refString="Miller, P. J. (1972) Generic status and redescription of the Mediterranean fish Gobius liechtensteini Kolombatovic, 1891 (Teleostei: Gobioidea), and its affinities with certain American and Indo-Pacific gobies. Journal of Natural History, London, 6, 395 - 407. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937200770371" type="journal article" year="1972">Miller 1972</bibRefCitation>
; Miller 1986; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFC63FD2BFBB6FD26" author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Miller, P. J. &amp; Patzner, R. A." box="[898,1110,685,712]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="169 - 176" refId="ref50370" refString="Ahnelt, H., Miller, P. J. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (1994) Systematics and distribution of two rare Mediterranean gobies, Corcyrogobius lichtensteini (Kolombatovic, 1891) and Odondebuenia balearica (Pellegrin &amp; Fage, 1907) (Teleostei: Gobiidae). Cybium, 18 (2), 169 - 176." type="journal article" year="1994">
Ahnelt 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFC39FD28FBEBFD26" box="[984,1035,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFB85FD2BFAA1FD26" author="Herler, J. &amp; Ahnelt, H. &amp; Scsepka, S." box="[1124,1345,685,712]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="489 - 507" refId="ref56151" refString="Herler, J., Ahnelt, H. &amp; Scsepka, S. (1999 a) Morphologische Untersuchungen an zwei hohlenbewohnenden Meergrundeln (Pisces: Gobiidae) des westlichen Mittelmeeres. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 101 B, 489 - 507." type="journal article" year="1999">
Herler 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFB54FD28FB09FD26" box="[1205,1257,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 1999a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFAAFFD2BFF34FD0D" author="Louisy, P." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F18FF8FFF26FD73FC7EFBEA" blockId="45.[151,1437,577,1432]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFE67FD73FCF6FCEE" bold="true" box="[390,790,757,783]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Background coloration brick red</emphasis>
(may vary from dark reddish brown to orangish brown, rarely yellowish) 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFE80FC9FFB9BFCD2" bold="true" box="[353,1147,793,819]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">with numerous narrow, transverse, bright blue to dark blue bars</emphasis>
(usually 10 to 15 visible on body), becoming more irregular on top of head (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F18FF8FFD06FCBBFCDCFCB6" box="[743,828,829,855]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1062,1086]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1037]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1435,181,1037]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 21. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Corcyrogobius liechtensteini (Kolombatović, 1891). Photo by S. Le Bris, Marseille, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601631/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Head sometimes darker, especially in males. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFAB4FCBBFAC0FC9A" bold="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Three continuous pale to bluish, more or less radiating bars extend from lower eye to underside of head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F18FF8FFACEFCE7FA70FC9A" box="[1327,1424,865,891]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,1212,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-41@23.[154,1434,1212,1864]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 20. Three pale, uninterrupted bars (marked with numbers) extending downwards from eye radiating downwards from eye to ventral side: A) C. liechtensteini, B) G. steinitzi. Photos by M. Kovačić (fishes photographed in a tank)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601629/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 20a</figureCitation>
). When present, 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFEA6FC03FD63FC7E" bold="true" box="[327,643,901,927]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">dark branchiostegal spots</emphasis>
located on lower head below each opercle are diagnostic (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F18FF8FFAD9FC03FA6FFC7E" box="[1336,1423,901,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1062,1086]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1037]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1435,181,1037]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 21. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Corcyrogobius liechtensteini (Kolombatović, 1891). Photo by S. Le Bris, Marseille, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601631/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Anterior nostril tube not contrastingly white. Dorsal fins usually bear rows of dark reddish spots that may coalesce in slightly oblique lines (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFE49FC4BFD93FC06" author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Miller, P. J. &amp; Patzner, R. A." box="[424,627,973,1000]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="169 - 176" refId="ref50370" refString="Ahnelt, H., Miller, P. J. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (1994) Systematics and distribution of two rare Mediterranean gobies, Corcyrogobius lichtensteini (Kolombatovic, 1891) and Odondebuenia balearica (Pellegrin &amp; Fage, 1907) (Teleostei: Gobiidae). Cybium, 18 (2), 169 - 176." type="journal article" year="1994">
Ahnelt 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFE1DFC48FDCBFC06" box="[508,555,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFD9DFC4BFC9DFC06" author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Patzner, R. A." box="[636,893,973,1000]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="529 - 544" refId="ref50234" refString="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (1996) Kryptobenthische Meergrundeln von den Balearen (Westliches Mittelmeer) mit Anmerkungen zum Unterartstatus von Chromogobius zebratus levanticus. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 98 B, 529 - 544." type="journal article" year="1996">Ahnelt &amp; Patzner 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
